HEADWORD: Paletot
<hw>Pal"e*tot</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>paletot</ets>, OF. <ets>palletoc</ets>, prob. fr. L.
<ets>palla</ets> (see <er>Palla</er>) + F. <ets>toque</ets> cap, and so
lit., a frock with a cap or hood; cf. Sp. <ets>paletoque</ets>.]</ety>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>An overcoat.</def> <au>Dickens.</au> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>A lady's outer garment, -- of varying fashion.</def>⟦br⟧
